Someone recently asked me what my favorite memory of 2023 is - and I realized that while I’ve had some incredible moments this year, it’s actually the challenges, lessons and growth that followed, I treasure the most this year. Those lessons (painful at times) have single-handedly shaped me into a more happy, healthy, peaceful human-being. Every single time something unfavorable, painful, upsetting etc happened and I truly paused and asked myself: “what’s the lesson in this for me” “if this were happening for my greater good, what reason would that be?” I always find a pot of GOLD🍯and that “unfavorable” thing ends up becoming one of the best things to happen to me. My favorite lesson learned this year: Every single thing is happening for my growth and greater good whether it looks that way or not. If i choose to explore the situation from a curious place as opposed to reactive place, I’ll find the gift. It’s all happening FOR US, and not TO us. So cheers🥂 to it ALL 💋💋💋 #2023 #lessonlearned #grow #discover #joy
